1
00:00:00,029 --> 00:00:01,069
Pleng! Go!

2
00:00:01,192 --> 00:00:02,192
Let go!

3
00:00:02,730 --> 00:00:04,101
Stop it!

4
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:05,130
Let go of me!

5
00:00:05,970 --> 00:00:06,970
Dad is sorry.

6
00:00:08,410 --> 00:00:10,334
I’ll make you become my brother.

7
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:11,970
I can remember now.

8
00:00:12,123 --> 00:00:13,432
I’m Tontharn.

9
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:26,712
(Mom wanted me to learn the violin)

10
00:00:26,741 --> 00:00:28,261
(So I can become good at it like Dad.)

11
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:37,192
Botpleng.

12
00:00:41,330 --> 00:00:43,905
(Mom probably wanted to hear Dad’s violin again.)

13
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:46,290
Botpleng.

14
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,076
Practice before the instructor arrives.

15
00:00:54,210 --> 00:00:55,210
Okay.

16
00:01:01,110 --> 00:01:02,741
But I can hardly remember

17
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:04,050
what it sounded like.

18
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:05,367
PETCHKLA THAYADON.

19
00:01:17,050 --> 00:01:18,378
(I met him)

20
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:20,763
(after following the sound of the violin)

21
00:01:20,785 --> 00:01:22,021
(all the way to that tree.)

22
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:42,450
Uh… Hi.

23
00:01:56,010 --> 00:01:57,170
You’re so good.

24
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:00,000
I’m also learning the violin.

25
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,738
My name’s Botpleng.

26
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:03,810
I’m Thun…

27
00:02:06,890 --> 00:02:07,890
I’m Tankhun.

28
00:02:09,905 --> 00:02:12,260
Nice to meet you, Tankhun.

29
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:39,701
(Tan made me enjoy the violin for the first time.)

30
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:44,305
(Just like knowing love for the first time.)

31
00:03:19,370 --> 00:03:21,112
(On Christmas of 2015)

32
00:03:21,650 --> 00:03:24,523
(the christmas songs could be heard
from the village’s office.)

33
00:03:28,890 --> 00:03:33,090
(I felt familiar with every melody I heard.)

34
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:35,505
(But in that moment, )

35
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:38,581
(I felt like I’ve actually become a melody)

36
00:03:38,618 --> 00:03:40,305
(when I’m in his embrace.)

37
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,698
(He was the final melody)

38
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,880
(that completed me.)

39
00:04:39,752 --> 00:04:41,070
I fear death

40
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,578
only after meeting you.

41
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:47,200
Melodies become beautiful

42
00:04:47,243 --> 00:04:48,763
only after I met you, too.

43
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:01,861
Come back quickly.

44
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,494
I’ll get treated quickly

45
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,589
and come back to see you.

46
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,501
You have to hurry back

47
00:05:08,530 --> 00:05:09,730
even if you haven’t recovered.

48
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:12,800
I’ll be back

49
00:05:12,843 --> 00:05:13,861
just in time to see you.

50
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:19,454
As long as you come back.

51
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:22,210
I’m going to wait for you right here.

52
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,356
I’ll be back.

53
00:05:39,930 --> 00:05:41,287
You have to come again next year.

54
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,250
Come again every year.

55
00:05:44,545 --> 00:05:45,545
On Christmas day,

56
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:47,992
we’ll meet here.

57
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:11,380
Mr. Pleng!

58
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,720
Tontharn!

59
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:18,567
You’re back?

60
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,640
Yes.

61
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:24,145
I’m back to see Mom Kan and you.

62
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:59,229
I was the one who caused Pleng’s death.

63
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:02,029
I’m Tontharn.

64
00:08:05,850 --> 00:08:06,850
Pleng.

65
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:16,800
Are you sure

66
00:08:17,670 --> 00:08:19,541
that you

67
00:08:20,570 --> 00:08:21,789
want all the memories back?

68
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,490
I want the truth.

69
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,516
I can remember now.

70
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,030
Tankhun!

71
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:48,310
Tankhun!

72
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:49,520
Tankhun!

73
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:50,730
Tankhun!

74
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,490
Tankhun!

75
00:08:51,512 --> 00:08:52,512
Pleng!

76
00:08:52,810 --> 00:08:53,810
Tankhun!

77
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:55,774
Pleng! I’m here.

78
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,323
Pleng, it’s me.

79
00:08:58,710 --> 00:08:59,710
Pleng.

80
00:09:07,745 --> 00:09:08,850
Pleng, it’s okay.

81
00:09:11,389 --> 00:09:12,400
I’m here.

82
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:16,070
I’m here.

83
00:09:26,550 --> 00:09:30,850
What you’re seeing now is the arrest

84
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:34,283
by the Behavioral Investigation Division or BID.

85
00:09:34,327 --> 00:09:35,794
They’ve asked for back-ups to arrest.

86
00:09:35,818 --> 00:09:38,072
Pol. Maj. Darakorn Decha—.

87
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:51,149
Tankhun.

88
00:10:06,974 --> 00:10:08,363
Everything has ended.

89
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:11,723
You’re alright now.

90
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:14,989
But I’m not Botpleng.

91
00:10:28,990 --> 00:10:32,778
You’ll always be Botpleng for me.

92
00:10:35,130 --> 00:10:36,130
You.

93
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:39,214
Only you.

94
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,316
I love you.

95
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,472
I love you.

96
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:05,978
I love you.

97
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,618
I love you too.

98
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,560
You.

99
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:16,705
This you.

100
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:20,698
It has always been you.

101
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,400
Stay with me.

102
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:56,290
Yesterday I was Botpleng.

103
00:11:58,750 --> 00:11:59,978
Then I woke up the next day

104
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:02,800
and I’m another person.

105
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,378
I used to think so, too.

106
00:12:10,610 --> 00:12:12,247
The day before, I was an orphan.

107
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,690
The day after that, I have parents

108
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,483
and two siblings.

109
00:12:19,460 --> 00:12:20,974
When you were adopted

110
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,352
what did you think of it?

111
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:25,818
I was pretty grown up back then.

112
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,858
So I didn’t want to be adopted that much.

113
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,650
But Thunphob’s parents

114
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:34,820
wanted someone whose bone marrow
that matches Thunphob’s.

115
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:37,600
And they found me.

116
00:12:41,690 --> 00:12:44,545
Back then, I thought it was good that way.

117
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,750
So that my life

118
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:48,618
can finally be of use.

119
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,370
In trade for them

120
00:12:52,407 --> 00:12:55,352
donating to the orphanage where I stayed.

121
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:05,985
When I get to see the sky

122
00:13:07,025 --> 00:13:09,030
and not being an orphan for the first time,

123
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
it was beautiful, though.

124
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:18,181
But for me, it’s huge

125
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,778
and frightening.

126
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,083
My name is “Tankhun”

127
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:29,170
so I wouldn’t forget

128
00:13:29,970 --> 00:13:31,970
whose gratitude I should repay.

129
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,270
Housemom.

130
00:13:34,810 --> 00:13:35,774
Dad and Mom.
Thunphob.

131
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:37,625
Jennaree.

132
00:13:39,309 --> 00:13:41,310
Everyone who’s been a family to me.

133
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:48,560
In that vast sky, I keep flying higher.

134
00:13:50,727 --> 00:13:52,014
But it gets more difficult.

135
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:05,970
Thunphob had depression.

136
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:08,145
He wanted to be like me.

137
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:09,570
He admired me.

138
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:14,967
So I had to be good to protect him.

139
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:16,785
I couldn’t be weak.

140
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,309
My parents died in a car accident.

141
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,570
Thunphob went missing.

142
00:14:24,392 --> 00:14:26,390
Jennaree distanced herself from the family.

143
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,390
Then one day, I understood.

144
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:33,170
That I

145
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:37,170
can’t replace anyone.

146
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:51,090
You are you, Tankhun.

147
00:14:55,025 --> 00:14:57,030
Even if I didn’t know your past at all,

148
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,869
I’d still love you.

149
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:04,807
Even if you’re not here,

150
00:15:06,230 --> 00:15:07,745
no one else could replace you.

151
00:15:08,610 --> 00:15:09,610
Yes.

152
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,338
You are also you.

153
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:18,116
You don’t have to replace anyone.

154
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:21,738
And nobody

155
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:25,054
can ever replace you.

156
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:51,690
I think I’m ready

157
00:15:53,230 --> 00:15:55,156
to return that Botpleng

158
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:58,036
to Thunphob.

159
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:38,385
My dad’s name is Tanu.

160
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,629
I’m Tanu’s son.

161
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:45,185
My mom is Napa.

162
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,570
My dad works for Khitakan.

163
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,290
She let me call her “Mom”.

164
00:17:08,010 --> 00:17:09,861
Napa has heavy hands.

165
00:17:13,190 --> 00:17:14,596
Do you want to give him to me?

166
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:17,898
I’ll raise him as if he’s my child.

167
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:19,760
I’ll give him everything like I give Botpleng.

168
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:21,869
I want a brother!

169
00:17:29,210 --> 00:17:31,090
Having you adore him

170
00:17:31,112 --> 00:17:33,389
is more than Tharn could ever ask for.

171
00:17:40,730 --> 00:17:44,116
(Mom’s angry that I keep being
with Mom Kan and Pleng.)

172
00:17:45,430 --> 00:17:46,865
What the hell are you doing?

173
00:17:46,909 --> 00:17:48,172
I’m going to hit him until he learns

174
00:17:48,196 --> 00:17:49,549
that he’s my son.

175
00:17:52,150 --> 00:17:52,603
Mom!

176
00:17:52,618 --> 00:17:54,152
Are you okay, Mom?

177
00:17:55,876 --> 00:17:56,876
Mom!

178
00:17:57,230 --> 00:18:00,480
(Finally, Dad moved us away from that house.)

179
00:18:00,792 --> 00:18:02,790
Why did you hit Mom, Dad?

180
00:18:09,352 --> 00:18:11,350
(Mom kept hurting me)

181
00:18:14,150 --> 00:18:15,563
(and others too.)

182
00:18:20,509 --> 00:18:22,560
(She killed the guy who came to collect debt)

183
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:24,741
(and Dad took her blame.)

184
00:18:27,310 --> 00:18:29,032
(Dad knew I loved Mom.)

185
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:30,843
(I would choose Mom.)

186
00:18:32,890 --> 00:18:34,181
Go back and live with Mrs. Kan.

187
00:18:35,780 --> 00:18:36,858
I’m begging you.

188
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:38,516
(Mom had to go back)

189
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,560
(because she didn’t have a choice.)

190
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:44,560
Pleng was nice to me as usual.

191
00:18:47,180 --> 00:18:49,367
We had so many things in common.

192
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:53,374
Our hand writings were similar.

193
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:59,236
We had similar thoughts.

194
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:05,992
He had me call him my older brother.

195
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:10,690
He took care of me

196
00:19:14,276 --> 00:19:16,280
and asked me to be his younger brother.

197
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:32,356
I will hide and film when she hits you.

198
00:19:33,210 --> 00:19:35,047
My mom knows someone at the MSDHS.

199
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:36,269
They can probably help us.

200
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,956
Will anything happen to Mom, Pleng?

201
00:19:47,290 --> 00:19:48,538
I don’t know.

202
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:51,592
But I don’t want anything to happen to you anymore.

203
00:19:55,210 --> 00:19:56,901
Your Mom should seek medical help, too.

204
00:20:10,570 --> 00:20:12,407
(Pleng was going to film a video)

205
00:20:12,443 --> 00:20:13,941
(when Mom hit me.)

206
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:18,940
You’re back, Mom?

207
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:24,232
I know you’re going to leave me, too.

208
00:20:24,261 --> 00:20:25,178
Just like your Dad.

209
00:20:25,221 --> 00:20:26,836
Just like your grandparents.

210
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,887
That’s not it, Mom.

211
00:20:28,923 --> 00:20:30,109
You just have to get help.

212
00:20:30,430 --> 00:20:31,745
I’m not sick!

213
00:20:32,916 --> 00:20:34,225
You bastard of a son!

214
00:20:34,269 --> 00:20:35,214
You’re horrible!

215
00:20:35,243 --> 00:20:37,178
You love them so much, huh?

216
00:20:37,214 --> 00:20:37,752
Mom!

217
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,840
- If you love them, then go!
- Stop it, Aunty!

218
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:43,461
You think you can take him from me so easily?

219
00:20:43,490 --> 00:20:44,494
It’s done.

220
00:20:47,990 --> 00:20:49,185
Are you okay, Tontharn?

221
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,800
Let’s go.

222
00:20:55,781 --> 00:20:56,781
Mom!

223
00:20:58,410 --> 00:21:00,261
Pleng! Pleng!

224
00:21:00,298 --> 00:21:01,298
Pleng!

225
00:21:01,910 --> 00:21:03,658
Pleng! Pleng!

226
00:21:04,390 --> 00:21:05,390
Pleng!

227
00:21:05,810 --> 00:21:06,810
Pleng!

228
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:07,980
Pleng!

229
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:09,592
You come with me.

230
00:21:10,501 --> 00:21:11,985
Come with me!

231
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:13,738
I told you to come out.

232
00:21:13,781 --> 00:21:16,130
Get out! Go!

233
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:17,512
Go!

234
00:21:17,556 --> 00:21:19,032
I told you to go!

235
00:21:19,076 --> 00:21:20,574
Go!

236
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:23,450
Come here!

237
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:24,590
Mom!

238
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:26,530
Mom!

239
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:28,740
I think the house is catching on fire.

240
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,025
Good! Let him die here.

241
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:33,832
Or would you like me to die?

242
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,923
Is this how you raise your kid?

243
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:40,036
F*ck!

244
00:21:40,072 --> 00:21:41,338
How did you get here?

245
00:21:41,381 --> 00:21:43,207
What the hell are you doing?

246
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:47,061
(I didn’t ask Dad how he got out of jail.)

247
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:50,356
(And when Mom said she’s taking me away, )

248
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:53,418
(was it away from Pleng)

249
00:21:54,270 --> 00:21:55,512
(or from Dad?)

250
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,480
Pleng!

251
00:21:58,890 --> 00:21:59,570
Pleng!

252
00:21:59,898 --> 00:22:00,898
Pleng!

253
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:02,870
Pleng!

254
00:22:03,003 --> 00:22:03,650
Pleng!

255
00:22:03,687 --> 00:22:04,687
Tontharn.

256
00:22:05,870 --> 00:22:07,258
Stop being crazy!

257
00:22:07,287 --> 00:22:08,287
F*ck!

258
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,360
What’s going on?

259
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:17,170
Let’s go.

260
00:22:17,214 --> 00:22:21,236
(I just thought I had to get him out of here.)

261
00:22:21,287 --> 00:22:23,069
Botpleng, where are you?

262
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,480
Tontharn!

263
00:22:24,523 --> 00:22:26,865
Hang in there, Mom Kan’s coming to get you.

264
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:32,894
Tontharn!

265
00:22:32,916 --> 00:22:33,916
Pleng!

266
00:22:35,730 --> 00:22:36,730
Pleng!

267
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,421
(Mom Kan was looking for Pleng.)

268
00:22:40,443 --> 00:22:41,443
Pleng!

269
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:43,745
(I thought no matter what, )

270
00:22:43,781 --> 00:22:45,432
(Pleng must have been safe.)

271
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:48,480
After that,

272
00:22:53,170 --> 00:22:54,894
I became Botpleng.

273
00:23:08,890 --> 00:23:10,778
I accidentally shot my wife.

274
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:15,265
Then I met Mrs. Kan, who was passed out.

275
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:18,298
I helped her out,

276
00:23:18,341 --> 00:23:19,981
but the flame was growing really quickly.

277
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,480
Mrs. Kan!

278
00:23:25,330 --> 00:23:26,330
Tontharn!

279
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:37,950
Tontharn!

280
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:39,400
Tontharn!

281
00:23:42,650 --> 00:23:44,181
Botpleng’s dead

282
00:23:44,210 --> 00:23:46,087
and Kan was alive but dead inside.

283
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:48,186
Luckily, there was still one more living person

284
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:49,738
she had to take care of.

285
00:23:51,820 --> 00:23:53,316
What’s going on, Mom?

286
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:55,810
Tontharn lost his memory.

287
00:23:56,110 --> 00:23:58,858
And to allow Khitakan to live on,

288
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,876
I decided to do the nastiest thing.

289
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:03,498
I’ve ever done.

290
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:14,305
Chomphon has studied hypnotization.

291
00:24:14,349 --> 00:24:16,080
We used to use this to treat my husband

292
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:19,454
when he was sick.

293
00:24:19,970 --> 00:24:23,083
Chomphon said the moment between
sleep and awake

294
00:24:23,580 --> 00:24:26,821
is the best time to hypnotize

295
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:29,861
and create Botpleng’s identity.

296
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:31,483
My name is Botpleng.

297
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:35,767
Dad likes to play this song for Mom and me.

298
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,487
Botpleng.

299
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:51,381
Botpleng, my son.

300
00:24:53,890 --> 00:24:56,021
Everytime I hear this song,

301
00:24:57,540 --> 00:24:59,818
it’s like I can hear my mom calling me.

302
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,850
It makes me realize

303
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:05,643
how much Mom loves me.

304
00:25:09,592 --> 00:25:12,552
I saw Tontharn turning into Botpleng.

305
00:25:13,930 --> 00:25:15,600
It would be better

306
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,574
for him not to remember that his dad is a murderer.

307
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:21,578
That his mom is a psychopath.

308
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:24,000
That was probably the best thing

309
00:25:24,058 --> 00:25:25,461
I could have done for him.

310
00:25:27,340 --> 00:25:28,785
So you killed Thunphob?

311
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:31,192
- Hurry up, Mom!
- Wait, wait, wait!

312
00:25:31,214 --> 00:25:32,989
Your uniform is still out of place.

313
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:36,400
You’re a junior now

314
00:25:36,698 --> 00:25:38,658
but you’re still not wearing your uniform neatly.

315
00:25:38,970 --> 00:25:40,930
If I’m all grown up

316
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:43,396
then you have to let me go to places alone.

317
00:25:44,910 --> 00:25:47,076
My boy is only 3 years old.

318
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:52,021
Mom, I’ll be back.

319
00:25:52,043 --> 00:25:53,563
I’ll get you soy milk on the way back.

320
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,465
Okay.
Let’s go.

321
00:25:55,141 --> 00:25:56,141
Let’s go.

322
00:25:57,950 --> 00:26:00,000
(Everything was going well)

323
00:26:00,036 --> 00:26:02,000
(had that boy not returned.)

324
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:06,960
(I asked Thunphob to meet up with me.)

325
00:26:06,989 --> 00:26:09,396
(To ask him not to take Botpleng away from me.)

326
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:11,803
Where’s Botpleng?

327
00:26:12,140 --> 00:26:13,752
The one who’s with you is not Botpleng.

328
00:26:14,130 --> 00:26:15,258
Botpleng’s dead.

329
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:17,710
You should leave.

330
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:20,392
Your Botpleng is no longer here.

331
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,240
You’re his mother.

332
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,392
Why did you do this to Pleng?

333
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,167
Even if he’s dead,

334
00:26:26,203 --> 00:26:28,109
you can’t replace him with anyone.

335
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:30,210
No one can replace Botpleng.

336
00:26:30,510 --> 00:26:32,390
You’re the one who doesn’t understand anything.

337
00:26:32,550 --> 00:26:35,083
I can’t live without Botpleng.

338
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,003
Not this Botpleng.

339
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:39,585
This is not my Botpleng

340
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,992
and I won’t let you replace him with anyone.

341
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,767
What are you going to do?

342
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:45,290
You can’t take Botpleng away from me.

343
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:56,669
Run away, Mrs. Kan.

344
00:26:57,510 --> 00:26:59,665
No one will take your Botpleng from you.

345
00:27:04,610 --> 00:27:06,298
(I left him in the car, )

346
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:08,116
(put the gear on neutral)

347
00:27:09,054 --> 00:27:10,770
(and pushed the car into the river.)

348
00:27:11,730 --> 00:27:13,265
Letting Botpleng’s secrets

349
00:27:13,630 --> 00:27:15,185
sink with him.

350
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:17,083
As deep as it can go.

351
00:27:18,807 --> 00:27:20,810
Where did you go after that?

352
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:23,105
I learned that.

353
00:27:23,134 --> 00:27:25,110
Mrs. Kan got into an accident that night.

354
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:43,949
I left on a ship and lived there.

355
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,985
Then I heard that the boy was murdered.

356
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:51,934
I knew his parents; they worked for Mrs. Kan.

357
00:27:51,963 --> 00:27:53,287
So I return right away

358
00:27:53,330 --> 00:27:54,669
to protect my son.

359
00:27:55,380 --> 00:27:56,974
What about the fishing net

360
00:27:57,820 --> 00:28:00,450
and the fact that you tried to hurt everyone?

361
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,709
The news said the murderer used a fishing net

362
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:05,847
so I tried to get one

363
00:28:05,876 --> 00:28:07,010
to follow his steps.

364
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:10,232
I hurt Tontharn

365
00:28:10,269 --> 00:28:13,192
because I didn’t want him to get involved in this.

366
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,680
What about the fact that you pleaded guilty

367
00:28:16,650 --> 00:28:18,058
and ran away from the court?

368
00:28:18,741 --> 00:28:20,740
I just didn’t want this case

369
00:28:21,150 --> 00:28:22,763
to lead back to Mrs. Khitakan.

370
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:25,550
As for running away from the court,

371
00:28:25,790 --> 00:28:26,872
I didn’t run,

372
00:28:26,901 --> 00:28:28,160
someone helped me.

373
00:28:29,910 --> 00:28:31,170
Inspector Dao?

374
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,923
There’s no one else.

375
00:28:40,152 --> 00:28:41,152
No.

376
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:43,461
I don’t believe it.

377
00:28:45,030 --> 00:28:46,327
I don’t believe you.

378
00:28:48,710 --> 00:28:49,883
Don’t lie to me.

379
00:28:50,740 --> 00:28:52,290
Don’t lie to me.

380
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,901
Because if everything were true,

381
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,054
everything you did

382
00:28:57,083 --> 00:28:58,570
would have been a waste, right?

383
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:02,557
And what would someone stupid like you

384
00:29:02,581 --> 00:29:03,585
know about it?

385
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,625
Yes, I’m stupid.

386
00:29:06,970 --> 00:29:08,029
But I’m not wicked.

387
00:29:08,990 --> 00:29:11,374
You are both stupid and wicked.

388
00:29:11,770 --> 00:29:14,080
How many innocent people did you kill?

389
00:29:14,109 --> 00:29:15,749
Just to take revenge on someone innocent.

390
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:19,832
So disgusting.

391
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:24,276
You are the disgusting one.

392
00:29:24,312 --> 00:29:25,312
Nim!

393
00:29:26,070 --> 00:29:26,938
Nim!

394
00:29:26,989 --> 00:29:28,370
Come back and release me!

395
00:29:28,407 --> 00:29:29,483
Nim!

396
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:31,883
You stupid lot!

397
00:29:31,912 --> 00:29:33,367
You’re the stupid one.

398
00:30:01,190 --> 00:30:02,190
I’m sorry.

399
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:04,770
Did I startle you?

400
00:30:07,350 --> 00:30:08,814
I’m the one to say sorry.

401
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:13,498
Sorry that Tankhun bothered you to stay with me.

402
00:30:16,460 --> 00:30:17,978
The Botpleng I know

403
00:30:18,730 --> 00:30:20,203
is you.

404
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:23,163
It has always been you, dude.

405
00:30:24,390 --> 00:30:25,840
You’re my Pleng.

406
00:30:30,970 --> 00:30:33,447
You’re still the same Botpleng for everyone.

407
00:30:34,390 --> 00:30:36,145
Nothing has changed.

408
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:20,887
You know what?

409
00:31:22,654 --> 00:31:24,400
I’ve never thought of this place as a home.

410
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,160
I’m living here

411
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:29,170
just because I have to stay

412
00:31:30,661 --> 00:31:32,007
to investigate Thunphob’s case.

413
00:31:34,990 --> 00:31:36,363
Look what happened now.

414
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,360
Over there.

415
00:31:57,570 --> 00:31:59,170
You cooked for me.

416
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:06,510
Here.

417
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:09,832
You helped me finish a jigsaw.

418
00:32:16,770 --> 00:32:17,770
At this place.

419
00:32:19,540 --> 00:32:21,069
You helped me shower.

420
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:27,207
I can’t remember

421
00:32:28,410 --> 00:32:29,985
how it felt

422
00:32:31,090 --> 00:32:32,385
to be alone anymore.

423
00:32:36,390 --> 00:32:37,498
I love you.

424
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:50,829
Can you take me to Botpleng?

425
00:32:53,540 --> 00:32:54,540
Sure.

426
00:32:55,830 --> 00:32:56,974
I love you.

427
00:33:38,490 --> 00:33:39,510
This place used to be the house

428
00:33:39,534 --> 00:33:41,541
with both my good and bad memories.

429
00:33:43,910 --> 00:33:45,454
I met Pleng here

430
00:33:49,030 --> 00:33:50,778
and lost Tontharn here.

431
00:34:23,687 --> 00:34:25,941
I used to come here with Pleng all the time.

432
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:30,203
He liked to come here to practice violin

433
00:34:31,170 --> 00:34:32,705
before his lover comes back.

434
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:35,658
Thun used to play the violin as a hobby.

435
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:39,258
But after returning to the UK, he acted up.

436
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:42,087
He refused to study criminology

437
00:34:42,116 --> 00:34:43,701
even when he already got accepted.

438
00:34:43,723 --> 00:34:45,585
He wanted to learn the violin professionally.

439
00:34:51,770 --> 00:34:54,901
How great must their loves have been?

440
00:34:56,450 --> 00:34:58,363
I used to want to meet Thunphob.

441
00:35:01,370 --> 00:35:03,090
I want to see them together for once.

442
00:35:09,670 --> 00:35:12,429
I think they’re together now.

443
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,116
You used to say

444
00:35:56,660 --> 00:35:57,687
the sound of a waterfall

445
00:35:57,723 --> 00:35:58,790
makes you feel at ease.

446
00:36:04,500 --> 00:36:06,400
I should have asked for a star.

447
00:36:11,090 --> 00:36:12,341
If you ask for it now

448
00:36:14,490 --> 00:36:16,090
doesn’t mean you’re not going to get it.

449
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:21,680
I thought you said
you were born to return the favors?

450
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:24,654
Why are you so spendy with your money?

451
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,610
I am returning the favor.

452
00:36:30,749 --> 00:36:33,585
Returning the favor for being with me.

453
00:36:45,590 --> 00:36:46,590
Here you go.

454
00:36:47,860 --> 00:36:48,860
What are you doing?

455
00:36:49,700 --> 00:36:51,156
Your stubble is starting to grow.

456
00:36:51,178 --> 00:36:52,210
Let’s give it some water.

457
00:36:52,450 --> 00:36:54,087
Water? Stubble?

458
00:36:55,510 --> 00:36:56,581
Stubble?

459
00:36:58,530 --> 00:36:59,636
Tankhun!

460
00:37:12,410 --> 00:37:14,843
I’ve never seen you with stubble.

461
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:18,392
But getting to see it,

462
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:20,276
it’s kind of cool.

463
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:24,283
I get to see this side of Dr. Tankhun,

464
00:37:24,650 --> 00:37:26,960
the super cool criminologist.

465
00:37:29,150 --> 00:37:30,181
And who was it

466
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:33,236
that made me have less time
to take care of myself?

467
00:37:34,150 --> 00:37:35,150
Hey.

468
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:35,985
Are you saying that

469
00:37:36,014 --> 00:37:37,374
you’re all worked up because of me

470
00:37:37,770 --> 00:37:39,770
that you don’t have time to take care of yourself?

471
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,920
I’m only kidding.

472
00:37:42,620 --> 00:37:44,894
I left it for you to shave it for me.

473
00:37:44,923 --> 00:37:47,250
So I can feel closer to you than before.

474
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,400
That’s why I left it for you to shave.

475
00:37:52,610 --> 00:37:54,378
I want to be closer to you.

476
00:37:57,530 --> 00:37:59,134
Is this not close enough?

477
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:03,905
I’m not sure.

478
00:38:04,630 --> 00:38:06,967
Sometimes I still think I’m not there yet.

479
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:15,578
How close do you want to come?

480
00:38:28,030 --> 00:38:29,338
What are you doing?

481
00:38:29,690 --> 00:38:31,527
This is a shaving blade. Don’t you see?

482
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:32,990
I’m not scared to get hurt.

483
00:38:34,938 --> 00:38:36,327
But I’m scared you'll forget.

484
00:38:37,350 --> 00:38:38,350
Forget that I love you.

485
00:38:39,018 --> 00:38:40,458
This you,

486
00:38:42,170 --> 00:38:43,520
who’s right in front of me.

487
00:38:47,310 --> 00:38:48,487
I won’t forget.

488
00:38:54,123 --> 00:38:55,381
You should finish shaving.

489
00:39:42,230 --> 00:39:43,230
Fresh vegetables.

490
00:39:43,258 --> 00:39:45,170
You can keep it for when you want to have it.

491
00:39:45,830 --> 00:39:47,716
For those, when they get cold,

492
00:39:47,745 --> 00:39:49,345
you just have to grill them again there.

493
00:39:49,450 --> 00:39:51,912
In the future, if we keep chickens,

494
00:39:52,290 --> 00:39:54,290
we’ll have fresh eggs every day.

495
00:39:56,890 --> 00:39:59,083
You’re going to have a farm?

496
00:39:59,990 --> 00:40:01,185
Hmm.

497
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:03,447
I don’t know.

498
00:40:04,410 --> 00:40:05,701
This is our house.

499
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,490
We need to discuss.

500
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:20,690
When I was young,

501
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:26,080
I only got to eat morning glories

502
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:27,898
because they grow back easily.

503
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:32,756
I ate bamboo shoots

504
00:40:33,934 --> 00:40:35,498
because we could find them.

505
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:38,720
I used to have chickens, too.

506
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:42,370
But when they stopped laying eggs,

507
00:40:45,170 --> 00:40:46,487
I would eat their flesh.

508
00:40:51,310 --> 00:40:52,625
Tontharn.'

509
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:55,054
He was Tontharn.

510
00:40:56,650 --> 00:40:57,934
Not Botpleng.

511
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:02,749
You used to be able to say it more directly, Tontharn.

512
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:12,520
Tan.

513
00:41:15,650 --> 00:41:17,149
I am Tontharn.

514
00:41:18,820 --> 00:41:20,210
I’m not Botpleng.

515
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:26,763
We aren’t in love.

516
00:41:28,510 --> 00:41:31,170
The person you love is Botpleng.

517
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:36,840
Yeah.

518
00:41:41,440 --> 00:41:42,676
Let’s break up.

519
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:49,934
Are you sure?

520
00:41:59,560 --> 00:42:00,560
I am.

521
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:04,720
Okay.

522
00:42:05,250 --> 00:42:06,327
Then let’s break up.

523
00:42:41,990 --> 00:42:42,990
Hello.

524
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,083
I’m Tankhun.

525
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:48,690
You’re Tontharn, right?

526
00:42:51,450 --> 00:42:52,967
It might seem too fast

527
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:55,585
but I think I like you.

528
00:42:57,410 --> 00:42:59,410
Can we get to know each other?

529
00:43:52,370 --> 00:43:54,290
I’ve also found a new life

530
00:43:54,327 --> 00:43:55,550
after meeting you.

531
00:43:56,580 --> 00:43:58,632
Not putting a label on it

532
00:43:58,676 --> 00:44:00,414
but so clear on the actions.

533
00:44:01,070 --> 00:44:02,625
Gen Z indeed.

534
00:44:02,661 --> 00:44:04,254
Whenever you want to fuel up,

535
00:44:04,290 --> 00:44:05,316
you can come and hug me.

536
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:06,946
Are you confessing your love to me?

537
00:44:06,970 --> 00:44:08,261
To a dog, maybe!

538
00:44:08,290 --> 00:44:09,927
I love the one I’m looking at!

539
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:11,978
Thun! Botpleng!

540
00:44:12,410 --> 00:44:14,080
I’m marrying Tontharn!
